<h2 id="exercises">Exercises</h2>

<p>Complete the following exercise to practice your new found git skills. Use the hints to reference the corresponding resources.</p>

<h3 id="create-your-first-git-project-repository">Create your first git project repository</h3>

<ol>
  <li>From the command line, create a new project repository</li>
  <li>Add a file to your project repository called ‚Äúindex.html‚Äù</li>
  <li>Add the following code to your ‚Äúindex.html‚Äù file</li>
  <li>Stage your index.html</li>
  <li>Commit your index.html</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="open-the-terminal-or-command-prompt-and-create-a-new-directory-my-repo-and-initialize-it-with-git-specific-functions">Open the terminal or command prompt and create a new directory, my-repo, and initialize it with git-specific functions</h3>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">mkdir </span>my-repo
git init my-repo
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="change-into-the-my-repo-directory">Change into the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">my-repo</code> directory</h3>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">cd </span>my-repo
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="create-the-first-file-in-the-project">Create the first file in the project</h3>

<p>Open the project directory with visual studio code and create a new file called <em>index.html</em></p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">touch </span>index.html
code index.html 
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="tell-git-to-upload-your-indexhtml-file-in-the-next-change">Tell Git to upload your index.html file in the next change</h3>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git add index.html
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="give-a-description-of-what-changed">Give a description of what changed</h3>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git commit <span class="nt">-m</span> <span class="s2">"add index.html to initial commit"</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="upload-your-changes-to-github">Upload your changes to GitHub</h3>

<p>Go to <a href="https://github.com">github.com</a> and login to your account.  Click the plus sign in the upper right corner, and then click ‚ÄúNew Repository‚Äù
Add a name, leave the rest of the options as defaults, and click ‚ÄúCreate Repository‚Äù.</p>

<p>After creating your repository, GitHub will display directions for uploading some code, but you are also welcome to follow the directions here:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git remote add origin https://github.com/&lt;YOUR-USERNAME&gt;/&lt;YOUR-REPO-NAME&gt;.git
git push origin main
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>This connects your local files to the files on github.com. If you refresh the repository page on GitHub, you should see your files</p>

<h3 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h3>

<p>Congratulations, you now have a GitHub account with a live project! Not only is this a great way to keep track of your changes as you go, but it is also a wonderful tool to put on your resume to show-off what you‚Äôve made.</p>

